value.title: Roger Stone reacts to pardon, calls Trump 'greatest president since Abraham Lincoln'
value.excerpt: In his first television interview since being pardoned by President Trump, longtime Republican consultant Roger Stone sounded off on being absolved and praised the president as the greatest since Abraham Lincoln.

value.title: Anti-Trump Lincoln Project ‘Republican’ says he’s reregistering Democrat
value.excerpt: A co-founder of the anti-Trump Lincoln Project group, a PAC formed by a group of “Never Trump” Rebublicans with the goal of aiding Joe Biden in the 2020 presidential race, said on his podcast that he will reregister as a member of the Democratic Party.

value.title: California conservatives rebuke Trump pardon of Duncan Hunter
value.excerpt: Trump granted a full pardon Tuesday to Hunter, who was set to begin an 11-month sentence at a federal prison in two weeks after pleading guilty to stealing campaign funds for personal use.

value.title: Trump pardons former campaign chairman Paul Manafort
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump has issued pardons and sentence commutations for 29 people, including former campaign chairman Paul Manafort and Charles Kushner, the father of his son-in-law

value.title: Trump issues 26 new pardons, including ones for Stone, Manafort and Charles Kushner
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump on Wednesday evening announced 26 new pardons, including ones for longtime ally Roger Stone, former campaign chairman Paul Manafort and White House senior adviser Jared Kushner's father, Charles.

value.title: Congressional GOP grapples with 'unhinged' Trump
value.excerpt: Even in his waning days in power, President Donald Trump is still finding ways to inflict his signature loyalty tests on the Republican Party.

value.title: Trump bashes Dems’ ‘extreme left-wing agenda,’ then pushes for $2,000 cash payments, something opposed by conservatives. It’s confusing.
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump stood in the White House’s Diplomatic Reception Room, holiday garland and gleaming ornaments draped on the fireplace behind him, and spoke into the camera not to deliver warm Christmas wishes,

value.title: Mike Pence reportedly in Vail Valley for the holidays
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence has chosen the Vail Valley as his holiday destination, according to multiple sources.

value.title: George Clooney on ‘The Midnight Sky’ and Donald Trump
value.excerpt: His new movie is on Netflix, but the actor-director says theaters won’t go away and Hollywood will be fine. He’s not so sure about Washington.

value.title: Milwaukee County spent nearly $1.7 million on Trump recount
value.excerpt: Newly released figures show that the presidential recount in Wisconsin’s Milwaukee County came in slightly under budget, at nearly $1.7 million

value.title: George Papadopoulos 'ecstatic' over Trump pardon, hints at possible lawsuit
value.excerpt: Former Trump 2016 campaign adviser George Papadopoulos celebrated the pardon President Trump granted to him while noting that he may not be done with his accusers.

value.title: Biden warns 'darkest days' are ahead for U.S....
value.excerpt: Watch "President-elect Joe Biden warns of 'darkest days' are ahead for U.S.", a CBSN video on CBSNews.com. View more CBSN videos and watch CBSN, a live news stream featuring original CBS News reporting.

value.title: Trump derails "Santa rally", Brexit deal hopes lift pound
value.excerpt: World stocks ticked up on Wednesday, as a last-minute intervention by President Donald Trump dampened positive sentiment over a U.S. stimulus deal, while the pound rose on the possibility of a Brexit agreement.

value.title: Trump grants full pardon to Russia probe figure George Papadopoulos
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump granted a full pardon on Tuesday to George Papadopoulos, a former campaign aide who pleaded guilty as part of the investigation into Russian meddling in the 2016 presidential election.

value.title: Israel hopes for rapprochement with fifth Muslim country before Trump exit - minister
value.excerpt: Israel is working towards formalising relations with a fifth Muslim country during U.S. President Donald Trump's term, which ends next month, an Israeli government minister told Ynet TV on Wednesday.

value.title: CAIR demands Biden 'defund' counterterror program
value.excerpt: The Council on American-Islamic Relations is urging President-elect Joe Biden to soften up on Islamic extremism in a new document on issues it hopes the new administration will address during its first 100 days.

value.title: Three Christmases: Highlights of Trump's previous Mar-a-Lago holiday stays
value.excerpt: Lago will have in store this year, but his previous holidays at the Southern White House have been notable and memorable. Trump arrived on Dec. 16 and departed on Jan. 1. On his way to Palm Beach, the president-elect first stopped in Orlando for a "thank you" rally for supporters.

value.title: Pence echoes Trump on election loss in West Palm speech to conservative youths
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence on Tuesday echoed his boss' defiance in the face of re-election defeat during a speech to young conservatives.

value.title: Biden says 'our darkest days with COVID are ahead of us, not behind us'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden spoke frankly in a rare address on the bleak reality of COVID-19 in the U.S., telling Americans "Our darkest days…are ahead of us, not behind us," during remarks on Tuesday.

value.title: News Wrap: Alex Padilla is tapped to fill Kamala Harris’ Senate seat
value.excerpt: In our news wrap Tuesday, California Secretary of State Alex Padilla is tapped to fill the U.S. Senate seat vacated by Vice President-elect Kamala Harris, the E.U.'s executive body calls for an end to travel bans aimed at confining a new COVID-19 strain in Britain,

value.title: Nancy Pelosi plans to pull Trump out of the White House 'by his hair': Report
value.excerpt: The House Speaker is said to have made the comments during discussions regarding a coronavirus relief package.

value.title: Lev Parnas files motion to dismiss, says he was selectively prosecuted to protect Trump
value.excerpt: Lev Parnas, the indicted associate of Rudy Giuliani, has filed a motion to dismiss the campaign finance charges against him, arguing he has been selectively prosecuted and blocked from providing information to lawmakers seeking to impeach President Trump.

value.title: Trump's main banker at Deutsche Bank announces her resignation
value.excerpt: The president's longstanding contact at the bank, Rosemary Vrablic, will step down on Dec. 31, though the reasons for her departure are unclear.

value.title: Even as he urges caution on COVID-19, Pence flies to Florida to speak at large event
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence has urged Americans to step up precautions, but he flew to Florida to speak to thousands at an indoor summit held by a conservative youth group.

value.title: Biden says cyberattack happened on ‘Trump’s watch when he wasn’t watching’
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is placing blame for the serious cyber hack of numerous federal government agencies and major companies on President Trump and pledged that “we will respond” when it’s determined which county is behind the damage.
